ZTRAKS.PBD
==========

(Daria Zieminska)

    Initializes Central Detector geometry for hit and track finding.
Must be included in every application that uses central tracks. Including
ZTRAKS does not mean track finding will be performed automatically for all 
events. Track finding is invoked by a call to ZTRAKS or ZTRALL.
To call track finding in selected roads do:

      CALL ZTRAKS(NR,PHIMIN,PHIMAX,THEMIN,THEMAX,PT,NZ,IDZ)

The routine returns NZ(1:NR) = number of CD tracks in roads and IDZ(1:NZ,1:NR)
= ID numbers of tracks in each road. 
To find all central tracks do:

      CALL ZTRALL

    All CD tracks found are stored in Zebra banks 'ZTRK'. They result from 
matching a CDC(or FDC) track with a VTX track. CDC,VTX and FDC tracks are 
stored in 'DTRK','VTXT' and 'FDCT', respectively. Zebra utility routines 
GTxxxx return contents of the appropriate track banks.
For more details examine sources in D0$ROOT:[TRACKING_UTIL...].
  


    o static parameter files for run number = xxxx 
        
        D0$CDC_GEO:STP_xxxx.ZEB   (example file D0$STP:CDC_STPFILE.DAT)
        D0$VTX_GEO:STP_xxxx.ZEB   (example file D0$STP:VTX_STPFILE.DAT)
        D0$FDC_GEO:STP_xxxx.ZEB   (example file D0$STP:FDC_STPFILE.DAT)
        D0$FDC_GEO:TRD_xxxx.ZEB   (example file D0$STP:TRD_STPFILE.DAT)
        
        For D0geant data default files from D0$STP are read automatically.


    o control parameters

        D0$TRACKING_UTIL$DZERO:ZTRAKS.RCP 
        D0$TRACKING_UTIL$CDC:DTRAKS.RCP 
        D0$TRACKING_UTIL$VTX:VTRAKS.RCP  
        D0$TRACKING_UTIL$FDC:FTRAKS.RCP  
        D0$TRACKING_UTIL$TRD:TRD.RCP  


    o data files

        Input to CD tracking may be generated by running D0GEANT using a file
        of ISAJET events (examples: D0$ROOT:[D0GEANT.DATA]MINBIAS.GEA and
        D0$ROOT:[D0GEANT.DATA]TTBAR.GEA). Use Geant data cards SCDC,SVTX,SFDC
        to select Geant output options: Sxxx(1)=1. for raw data, Sxxx(2)=1.
        for ideal hits. 

